  "decision_notes": "The problem is decomposed into checking the existence of k(n)=1, then k(n)=2, and finally investigating k(n)=3 based on the results of the previous steps.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=1 is possible. This occurs if 2023*n is a power of 2 for some integer n. Check if 2023 is a power of 2 by examining its prime factorization. If it is not, conclude that k(n)=1 is impossible."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Determine if k(n)=2 is possible. This occurs if 2023*n = 2^a + 2^b for some integers a and b. Check if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b for any integers a, b. If no such a and b exist, investigate whether k(n)=3 is possible (i.e., if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c)."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the results from helper_1 and helper_2 to determine the minimum k(n). If helper_1 finds k(n)=1 is possible, the answer is 1. If helper_1 says no and helper_2 finds k(n)=2 is possible, the answer is 2. If both are impossible, the agent will evaluate the findings for k(n)=3 to determine the final minimum value."
}
```

